snippet.textDisplay: I love how you covered problems that happen all the time with first-time filmmakers or film students! As an actor who went to film school for post-production. I died on the inside when I acted in a freshmen SCAD student film and found out that they let them check out a 4K camera and good lighting equipment but would not let them check out sound equipment! A fucking Tascam DR-40 takes maybe 20 minutes to fully teach someone how to use it for say a student film and is cheaper than all the other equipment you let them check out?  Don't get me wrong, I had an absolute blast working on their film and they had a wonderful concept and were a wonderful team to work with! But sound equipment would have made it so much better. Also even if your microphone is plugged directly into the camera, PLEASE RECORD ROOMTONE!  Also I want to point out that SCAD student are no longer required to finished their films. That needs to change!
snippet.textOriginal: I love how you covered problems that happen all the time with first-time filmmakers or film students! As an actor who went to film school for post-production. I died on the inside when I acted in a freshmen SCAD student film and found out that they let them check out a 4K camera and good lighting equipment but would not let them check out sound equipment! A fucking Tascam DR-40 takes maybe 20 minutes to fully teach someone how to use it for say a student film and is cheaper than all the other equipment you let them check out?  Don't get me wrong, I had an absolute blast working on their film and they had a wonderful concept and were a wonderful team to work with! But sound equipment would have made it so much better. Also even if your microphone is plugged directly into the camera, PLEASE RECORD ROOMTONE!  Also I want to point out that SCAD student are no longer required to finished their films. That needs to change!
